5 Section 2. Section 61-4-201, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "61-4-201. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply unless the context clearly
7 indicates otherwise:
8 (1) "Community" means the relevant market area of a franchise. For the purposes of this part, the
9 relevant market area of a franchise is the county or counties in which the franchisee is located.
10 (2) "Distribute" means to sell new motor vehicles other than at retail or to enter into a franchise
11 agreement authorizing a dealer to buy new motor vehicles for resale or to service motor vehicles under a
12 manufacturer's or distributor's warranty.
13 (3) "Distributor" or "wholesaler" means a person who sells or distributes a line-make of new motor
14 vehicles to new motor vehicle dealers in this state or who maintains distributor representatives in this state.
15 (4) "Distributor branch" means a branch office maintained or availed of by a distributor or
16 wholesaler for the sale of a line-make of new motor vehicles to new motor vehicle dealers in this state for
17 directing or supervising its representatives in this state.
18 (5) "Factory branch" means a branch office maintained or availed of by a manufacturer for the sale
19 of a line-make of new motor vehicles to distributors or for the sale of new motor vehicles to new motor vehicle
20 dealers in this state or for directing or supervising its representatives in this state.
21 (6) "Franchise" means a contract and any agreed-to amendments between or among two or more
22 persons when all of the following conditions are included:
23 (a) a commercial relationship of definite duration or continuing indefinite duration is involved;
24 (b) the franchisee is granted the right to:
25 (i) offer, sell, and service in this state new motor vehicles manufactured or distributed by the
26 franchisor; or
27 (ii) service motor vehicles pursuant to the terms of a franchise and a manufacturer's warranty;
